{
  "stem": "2435.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She even went outside and sat on benches which were not marked for Jew.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And funny enough, she was not caught.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But she was like that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She was never afraid.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That can never happen.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When it really came to the point where she heard that so many people were deported, then she-- only her eyes opened.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But she was very hopeful that we would still get a visa for her once we were in America.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when we-- I remember when we separated from her on the day of our emigration, in April '41, she said goodbye to us and said, don't worry.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You will get the visa for me very soon, and I will see you.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And our Nana was there, too, and she said the same.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She said, you will get the visa for her and I will take care of Grandma until-- until she cannot live any more here, but I will be with her all the time and I will try to bring her food.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Nana was absolutely wonderful person.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It helped.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, he requested that the visa would be sent-- it was an urgent request.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he said, they must get out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he also gave a letter about my father, whom he knew and with whom he had worked for so many years in Berlin, telling of his very good contact and what a wonderful physicist he was.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he said in that letter that it was very urgent that we leave because I was sick and would only find health again in a new country where one wasn't under oppression.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
